block vars
  - var pageDescription = 'Airport Codes: A site dedicated to making sense of those three-letter codes.'
  - var bodyClass = 'work layout-sub'

extends ../layout

block title
  | Airport Codes - 

block content

  .content-container.project-detail

    h1
      a.project-title(href='http://airportcod.es')
        span.title Airport Codes
        span.url airportcod.es

    img.main-image(src='/assets/images/work-airport-codes.jpg')

    blockquote Airport Codes has us diverting more time from work this week than our Facebook feeds.
      cite Chuck Thompson, CNN

    p Every airport has a unique three-letter IATA code. Some make sense if you know the city or the name of the airport and others, well, what the heck? Turns out there’s usually a reasonable explanation.
    P The site features over 1000 airports and includes an airport from every country that has one.
    p Airport Codes was featured on #[a(href='http://www.vox.com/2015/3/24/8284391/airport-codes') vox.com], #[a(href='http://www.cnn.com/2015/04/01/travel/airport-codes/index.html') cnn.com], and NPR’s #[a(href='http://hereandnow.wbur.org/2015/04/01/airport-codes-mysteries') Here & Now].
    ul
      li
        a.emoji-link(href='http://airportcod.es')
          span.em.em-globe_with_meridians
          span airportcod.es
      li
        a.emoji-link(href='https://github.com/lynnandtonic/airport-codes')
          span.em.em-octocat
          span Contribute via GitHub

    p #[a.back(href='/') ← Back to projects list]